The Nigerian Society of Engineers has conferred fellowship on Engr. Amb. Solomon Emhonbotti,JP, FCAI and  57 other deserving Engineers.
The award was conferred on them at NSE’s 20th Fellowship Conferment Ceremony at Chida Event Centre, Utako,Abuja, on Friday, July 22, 2022.
Engr. Solomon Emhonbotti, the Labour Party Candidate, House of Representative Esan west, Esan Central & Igueben Federal Constituency, alongside 57 others were conferred with the highest grade of the engineering profession and duly recognized as fellows of the revered engineering body.
The Guest lecturer of the Event called on Engineers across Nigeria to take full advantage of new developments, and emerging opportunities in Engineering Technology in Africa.
READ ALSO: FG tasks engineers on innovation for economic development
And stress that Nigeria depends on Engineers to attain national growth and development.
A Consummate and COREN Registered Engineer Solomon Emhonbotti has been an active member of the following professional bodies; The Nigerian Society of Engineers (NSE), Council of Registered Engineers of Nigeria (COREN), Institute of Industrial & Systems Engineers (IISE), Nigerian Institute of Power Engineers (NIPE), Nigerian Institute of Electrical Electronic Engineers (NIEEE), Fellow Institute of Corporate Administration of Nigeria (FCAI) and National American Society of Black Engineers.
Engr. Solomon Emhonbotti has written and presented several technical papers at both local and international journals and foras.
